<h1>Problem 2175 - 1999 IMOSL, A4, AC</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Prove that the set of positive integers cannot be partitioned into three nonempty subsets such that, for any two integers \(x,y\) taken from two different subsets, the number \(x^2-xy+y^2\) belongs to the third subset.</p>
